output.dependency: The name of the beer (column 2) determines its type (column 3), as each beer name is associated with a specific beer style.
The alcohol by volume (ABV) percentage (column 5) may be semantically related to the sweetness or flavor profile represented in the other column (column 6), although column 6 may contain null values.
The brewery name (column 8) typically corresponds with the location (column 9) given the known operational structure of breweries being situated in cities.

The common identifier for the entries (column 7), likely a unique identifier for the record, does not have a direct dependency with the state abbreviation (column 10), however they both relate to the same brewing company and city.
